title: At least six dead after fire at New Zealand hostel
description: At least six people have died after a fire broke out overnight at a four-storey hostel in New Zealand.

title: Four dead and several others wounded in US shooting
description: At least four people have been killed and several others injured in a shooting in the US.

title: FBI lacked 'actual evidence' to probe Trump-Russia links, report finds
description: The FBI lacked any "actual evidence" to begin investigating potential links between Donald Trump's 2016 presidential campaign and Russia, a report has concluded.

title: Royal Navy sailor found dead in Stockholm - as four people arrested
description: An investigation has been launched after a Royal Navy sailor was found dead in a residence in Sweden.

title: Musk tells Macron he had to 'sleep in the car' before meeting French president
description: Elon Musk has been heard telling French President Emmanuel Macron that he had to "sleep in the car" before their meeting in Paris - hours after the billionaire was seen partying in Mexico and Los Angeles.

title: The battle for Bakhmut: Ukrainian city a smoking ruin as Russians forced back in disarray
description: An armoured personnel carrier kicks up dust as it careers across the drying land.

title: Microsoft-Activision Blizzard £55bn merger approved by EU - despite UK rejection
description: The $68.7bn (£55bn) mega merger between Microsoft and game developer Activison Blizzard has been approved by the European Union, just weeks after it was blocked by the UK.

title: Cadbury working on low sugar chocolate bars, as WHO recommends avoiding sweeteners for weight control
description: Cadbury is "working hard" to produce alternative 75% less sugar, fat and lower calorie versions of products, as the World Health Organisation (WHO) recommended avoiding sweeteners for weight control.

title: Sweeteners do not have long-term effect on weight loss, says WHO
description: People should avoid using sweeteners for weight control, the World Health Organisation (WHO) has recommended.

title: What is a run-off election, how will it work in Turkey and what is a kingmaker?
description: After a tight race between Turkey's main presidential candidates, voters will return to the polls in two weeks to vote again on who will lead the country.

title: Hitler speech played on Austrian train's loudspeaker
description: Two Austrian men have been charged after speeches by Nazi leader Adolf Hitler were reportedly played on a train's loudspeaker system.

title: British expat accused of wife's murder tells court she 'begged him' to help her die
description: A British expat accused of murdering his terminally ill wife in Cyprus has told a court she "cried and begged" him to help end her life.

title: Photo emerges of Belarusian leader after health rumours
description: A photo of Alexander Lukashenko, the president of Belarus, has been published by a national state news channel after speculation that he was seriously ill.

title: Where is Alexander Lukashenko? Russia refuses to comment on Putin ally's health
description: Russia has refused to comment on the health of Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko amid speculation that he is seriously ill.

title: Newspaper apologises and takes down 'hoax' AI-generated article
description: The Irish Times has apologised after it published an opinion article that was generated by artificial intelligence.

title: UK pledges hundreds of new attack drones to Ukraine ahead of Zelenskyy-Sunak summit
description: The UK has pledged to send hundreds of new long-range attack drones to Ukraine ahead of Volodymyr Zelenskyy's meeting with Rishi Sunak today.

title: Six more lions speared to death by Kenyan herders just days after one of the country's oldest lions was killed
description: Six lions have been killed by herders in Kenya, just days after one of the  country's oldest lions was also fatally targeted.
